            {
               "text": "<p><table><tr><th>Quantum atom</th><th>DNA molecule</th><th>Living Beings</th></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgQA\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgQA', '0%')\" src=\"images/Atom_Quantum.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgDNA\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgDNA', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/DNA.png\" style=\"width:90%\" /></td><td><img id=\"img2Cat\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img2Cat', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/CatsCirusUrraca.jpg\" style=\"width:70%;\"></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 70%;\"><b>Figure 2</b>: Simplified representation of a hydrogen atom on the left, a DNA molecule in the center, and living beings on the right.</td></tr></table></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Superposition\n\nJust like nature, humans also build structures by combining smaller parts. An example of this is **Temple 16 of Copán**, in Honduras, which underwent various construction phases over a span of approximately 400 years. As shown in Figure 3, the first phase involved the construction of a small structure. Over time, additional layers were added, eventually resulting in the larger structure we see today",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "daae87a2-5fa9-43d1-88fb-6713b25d50d5",
                     "text": "Tuarez Mejia, L. F.",
                     "page": "pp. 120-128",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": "."
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgCopanTemple\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgCopanTemple', '0%')\" src=\"images/Copan/Temple16Copan.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 3</b>: Poster at the archaeological site of Copán (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('1e007481-9bd3-4a09-ad4d-6e812fe79641'); return false;\">Instituto Hondureño de Antropologia e Historia, <htdate0></a>). Photo taken on <htdate1>, during a visit to the site.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
