               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_example",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Beginning Small\n\nWhen observing giant structures, such as the pyramids found in the Americas (<i>Abya Yala</i>), it becomes evident that the mountains near these archaeological sites served as inspiration for their design. These structures feature wide bases that gradually narrow as they ascend to the top, as illustrated in **Figure 4**.\n\nIn addition to this natural inspiration, recent discoveries have revealed the use of small maquettes as models to guide the construction of the sacred city of Caral in Peru",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "720f6dfd-4b86-4e07-a887-1010e1041a4d",
                     "text": "Ruta Caral",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
